text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
the 5 things you need to know // about what happens at 5 years sober 😳💔
.

it’s like a great secret.
but with subtle sprinkled clues.
phrases are sometimes said around the rooms..
. ⚡️ “don’t kill yourself in the first 5 years because you’ll be killing the wrong person”
. ⚡️ “there’s a big boom at 5. it’s the sound of your head coming out of your @ss”
. ⚡️ “enjoy early sobriety because 5 is when you get your feelings back.”
.

if you’re around 5 years sober.
or maybe just feeling five.
this is for you…
.

1.  the hood pops open
.

there’s “lower hanging fruit” in early sobriety.
like how to stop having panic attacks.
becoming less emo reactive.
and learning how to be sober through all of the life things…
.

it’s only a bit later.
typically between 4 and 6 years.
or even much further down the sobriety line.
where the hood pops open.
.

and we have access to the pain that the addiction masked.
.

omg. 🤯
.

the anxiety was a warning light on the dashboard.
saying “hey check under the hood!!”
but we drank, smoke, ate, sexed.
.

we covered the warning light, or feelings, instead of looking under the hood.
instead of directly addressing the emotional pain.
.

so yea, happy five, welcome to your original pain.
.

no worries, this is good, keep reading 😉
.

2.  second dark night of the soul
.

the dark night of the soul is characterized by two distinct things.
.

a — an emotional release/purge. 
b — an identity crises.
.

are you feeling slammed with anger, sadness, as well as feeling l o s t?
.

could be your second dark night.
continue 👇🏽
.

3.  commit to no longer rejecting yourself
.

this is imperative if you wan to truly heal.
.

if you want to get f r e e
.

otherwise you’ll continue on blotting out your joy, happiness and vibrancy with secondary additions in sobriety.
.

like swiping right, netflix, chocolate, working out…
living as a slave to something instead of shining your bright light. 🌟 .

masking how you feel is self rejection.
this is why you feel l o s t.
.

because you’ve never stopped long enough to actually get to know yourself.
how could you when you’re constantly rejecting how you feel with secondary addictions.
.
continues in comment👇

text:
(parte ii) desperté a todos en casa cuando volví inesperadamente en llanto y temblando. fuimos a levantar la denuncia en el ministerio y no quise que el doctor me revisara. no quería que me vieran y traspasaran mi entidad de nuevo. no así. no ellos. no nadie. no más.
la ley en méxico es terrible y desistí de continuar las investigaciones. 
mi familia no conoció la historia completa por poco más de una década, que decidí hablarlo abiertamente poco a poco. 
vi desgarrarles el corazón a mi familia y sabía que era esa la razón por la que no lo había hecho antes a de más de la vergüenza que me cargaba y la opinión de terceros. 
salté de una zona de depresión a otra por tantos años; entonces, el yoga sucedió. 
me enseñó que yo no era una víctima si no una sobreviviente que se aferró a todo lo que pudo. tuve mis altibajos y mis crisis pero no me rendí. 
me enseñó que no soy lo que me pasó si no lo que decido hacer con eso. .
y decidí hacer esto público cuando un ídolo mío a quién jamás imaginé que  hubiera vivido algo así, lo hizo. 
es cuestión de alzar la voz y de acompañar a otros seres humanos en su lucha, de hacerles saber que no están solos en ese rincón sometidos, tragados por la obscuridad, mudos como yo me sentí una vez. .
que hay mucho más camino después del golpe, que el mundo no es el enemigo. 
aquí estoy para escucharlos o tomarles la mano, o gritar juntos. o simplemente guardar silencio. 
está la cicatriz de una herida que una vez fue profunda y sin embargo hay tanta belleza y tanta magia en el universo ocurriendo cada segundo. y nosotros tan pequeños... y tan poderosos. .
aquí estoy. sobreviví y tú también lo harás. #yoga #cdmx #yogalifestyle #swag #instacool #tweegram #progress #yogagirl #yogateacher #igers #yogagram #igersmexico #follow #picoftheday #webstagram #instadaily #20likes #all_shots #instagramers #yogapractice #yoga_feature #yogalifestyle #lifestyle #instagood  #igyogacommunity #practiceyogachangeyourworld #onebreathatatime #metoo

text:
[#미투, 광장액션] “세상을 부수는 말들”에 참여할 218명의 참여자를 모집합니다🔥

#미투 는 이 사회의 성차별적 사회구조를 드러낸 ‘세상을 부수는 말’임 동시에 ‘세상을 다시 세울 말’이기도 합니다. 성평등한 세상을 다시 만들기 위해 광장에 당신의 목소리를 채워주세요. 👉우리가 다시 광장에 모야야 하는 이유
1) 바뀌지 않는 현실을 부수기 위해!
2) 성폭력 피해생존자에게 향했던 비난의 시선을 사건의 책임자인 가해자에게 돌리고, 국가에 제대로 된 미투 대책을 촉구하기 위해!
3)아무리 외쳐도 듣지 않는 사람들을 변화시키기 위해!

text:
never ever stop. 
no matter what happens. always keep moving forward. 
progress is progress. no matter how fast or slow you go. no matter how quickly you see others moving through life. 
don’t worry about them, it’s their life to live not yours. 
don’t put your life on hold for anyone or anything. 
time is an underrated and under appreciated gift that so many of us take for granted. 📸 : @chris_pantera

text:
על השירה שכתבה נגד הכיבוש שילמה דארין טאטור במאסר. על המאבק שלה באלימות נגד נשים בחברה הערבית היא עלולה לשלם בחייה. היא עברה שני אירועים טראומטיים: השני הוא המשפט המתוקשר שלה, שנמשך שלוש שנים, שבהן שהתה 97 ימים במעצר, שנתיים וחצי במעצר־בית וחודשיים בכלא כאסירה המרצה את גזר דינה. הטראומה הראשונה התרחשה מאז שהיתה בת שבע ועד שמלאו לה 12: "הכיבוש הגברי והכיבוש הישראלי חשבו שיסתמו את הפה שלי, אבל קורה ההפך. הם נתנו לי יותר כוח. כל החיים מנסים להשתיק אותי, אבל נמאס לי לשתוק" - לינק לראיון המלא עכשיו בסטורי שלנו
.

text_retweet:
**trigger warning** #domesticabuse
one of the hardest things i’ve ever done was share this experience. i kept it a secret from most people for just about a decade. 
#repost @sabrinasee
・・・
enjoy this #fbf of me and the boyfriend who hit me. this was about a month after it happened. no one really knows what goes on privately between two people. even if someone had asked, i wouldn’t have told. i was too prideful and wanted to fix it or him or maybe even me. instead i just descended deeper and deeper into the pit of hell. super glad that shit is over. if i learned anything it’s relationships can never be perfect but you have to be honest with yourself and your partner if you want to have a good one. hopefully, i can carry that lesson and the boundaries i continue to learn into all my future ones.

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
her world was drained of color. the flowers dripping gold once before were void, turned gray and black as night. 
the stars in the sky seemed to dim, the sunshine no longer seeming to melt its way in, beyond the shadow of doubt, she had become a new person inside and out.
"you did a bad thing," she whispers solemnly, her voice lacking tone, the colors in her eyes had faded into obsidian, and the scratches in her throat were evident. 
she was staring into the face of a demon, the one that stole her youth, and her freedom. she was telling the morning star himself the faults that he held, his worst failing. 
because, they had told her in the church that the devil lived in creatures like him, lived in the souls of those who make choices like him, 
but it had also told her to forgive his mortal sin.
and that was what brought her here in front of him.
"you did a bad thing," this time a scream, a howl into the darkness. 
it was a battle cry, as if to warn him that the distance between them was a mere five feet apart, 
that she was ready to rip out his heart and feed it to wolves, 
to tear him apart with the truth that she told.
she had tried to convince herself it hadnt happened, not anyone else that it had.
and now she was in the mouth of the devil, the belly of the beast, ready to set him ablaze.
she was ready to claw into him, to let the devil rip him to shreds from the inside out.
"you did a bad thing," a whisper again, and he was preparing himself for all-out war, for the waves to come crashing down onto the shore.
but this time, she held the strength of a thousand suns, 
she knew that she had already won. 
she knew that god himself would deliver what's to come, 
and she almost wished for mercy, 
despite the things that this man had done.
and so this time, the words that came off her tongue, were nothing but a bitter, "you know what you've done." ☆

text:
si je n’écris plus rien en ce moment c’est parce que ce que je vis est trop profond. trop dur à dire, trop dure à exprimer, à expliquer. 
je crois qu’on appelle ça une dépression. enfin le mot je ne l’aime pas, et c’est d’ailleurs la première fois que je l’emploie à mon égard. 
j’ai du mal à le dire car pourtant j’arrive à rire, j’arrive à rigoler, j’arrive à faire comme si de rien été. (il y’a des jours où j’y arrive moins bien).
quand on me voit comme ça, en aucun cas on peut se douter des douleurs profonde que j’ai au fond de moi. 
en société je suis une fille plutôt souriante, pleine de bonne humeur (enfin surtout avec ma famille). mais par compte dès que je me retrouve seule, je déprime, je pleure. 
il y a quelques semaines, j’ai fait une crise d’angoisse tellement forte, à pleurer, à ne plus pouvoir respirer, à suffoquer, à hurler de douleur. j’avais tellement mal à l’intérieur que j’ai voulu l’extérioriser... je n’en suis pas fière, j’ai même une honte absolue. sincèrement j’ai voulu en finir. pourtant au fond de moi je ne veux pas mourir, je veux seulement arrêter de souffrir. 
je veux seulement arrêter de voir son visage dans tous les regards des hommes. 
je veux seulement arrêter de voir cette scène en boucle, comme un vieux films dont une scène nous marque. 
je veux seulement que cette douleur cesse, et parfois je me dis que la mort sera mon seul soulagement. mon seul échappatoire. 
je sais bien que c’est pas très gai, et je déteste les gens qui écrivent des choses comme ça. car sincèrement personne a envie de lire ça.. je le sais bien. 
mais à l’heure actuelle je ne sais même plus qui je suis. 
on dis qu’il faut se perdre pour mieux se retrouver. bah moi je suis complètement perdu et pour l’instant je ne me retrouve pas du tout. 
j’enchaîne conneries sur conneries. des choses que je ne peux même pas dire, des choses que personne ne sais... cette vie qui ne me ressemble pas, et pourtant devenu mienne. .
.
.
.
#depression #suicide #scarification #douleurprofonde #douleurinterne #crisedangoisse #moiaussi #metoo #viol #agressionsexuelle #connerie #souffrance #pleurs ##demerde

text_retweet:
many thanks to @captainsunnshine for catching who i am at this exact moment in time. those of y’all who have known me for a minute have watched me walk through hell and back for the past two years. i arrived in ny last week a survivor of five assaults, the remaining living member of a family business i started helping with when i was seven, having just been through a breakup so brutal i still can’t quite believe it actually happened. this time last year i was so overcome with trauma and grief that i literally couldn’t walk. i gave up on my playing and what’s worse, i was fully ready to give up on myself. about a dozen people across the globe, however, chose not to give up on me.  the most important of these is my pops, who left this plane all too soon but also left me with a legacy to uphold in @theory4guitar. the rest have been the colleagues and students who each decided, on their own, it wasn’t time for me to put it down just yet. the cumulative value of what y’all see in me that i stopped being able to see in myself is just...i literally do not have the words. so yea, it’s just a guitar competition and this one in particular is mostly about having fun.  but it’s been a long road from 2010 to 2018 and the fact that i am able to be here, standing for this photo at all is a goddamn miracle. thank you. 🙏🙏🙏🙏🙏🎸. . . . . . . . . .  #femaleguitarist #chickswithpicks #godin #godinguitars #brooklyn #womenwhorock #survivor #metoo #sessionguitarist #greenpoint #shredforyourlife #nycrocknroll #blondesplaymorenotes #nyc . . . #repost @marcotron15
・・・
wanted to congratulate @shred4yourlife champion lily maase @msmaize on her big win on monday👑. lily now holds titles in 2010 and 2018. when she’s not lopping heads off at guitar battles you can find her teaching guitar in manhattan, new mexico and all around the world now via skype, running a publication called guitar dad publications ( she and her father put out a book called @theory4guitar ), playing in g&r tribute band called @therocketqueens, and now i’ve been told that she started a new band called the reckoning that comes out soon. thanks for taking the time to join us lily! ❤️ photo 2 @captainsunnshine

roger waters - homem das águas de março brasileiro por coração. peço desculpas pelo meu povo que o vaiou por motivos excusos, alheios a nós. somos roqueiros e como um bom, sempre protestantes. resistência, contra o fascismo, nem fodendo. não, mil vezes ele não, nem fodendo um bilhão de vezes não. no fucking way! seja sempre bem vindo sem censura. a censura é a ausência do intelecto criado pelos humanos ignorantes. a censura quer nos calar, mas nem fodendo por que somos a resistência sem muros.

text:
como nosso pais •
•
menu

como nossos pais

belchior ￼

não quero lhe falar
meu grande amor
das coisas que aprendi
nos discos
quero lhe contar como eu vivi
e tudo o que aconteceu comigo

viver é melhor que sonhar
eu sei que o amor
é uma coisa boa
mas também sei
que qualquer canto
é menor do que a vida
de qualquer pessoa

por isso cuidado, meu bem
há perigo na esquina
eles venceram e o sinal
está fechado pra nós
que somos jovens

para abraçar meu irmão
e beijar minha menina na rua
é que se fez o meu lábio
o meu braço e a minha voz

você me pergunta
pela minha paixão
digo que estou encantado
como uma nova invenção
vou ficar nesta cidade
não vou voltar pro sertão
pois vejo vir vindo no vento
o cheiro da nova estação
e eu sinto tudo na ferida viva
do meu coração

já faz tempo
e eu vi você na rua
cabelo ao vento
gente jovem reunida
na parede da memória
esta lembrança
é o quadro que dói mais

minha dor é perceber
que apesar de termos
feito tudo, tudo, tudo
tudo o que fizemos
ainda somos os mesmos
e vivemos
ainda somos os mesmos
e vivemos
como os nossos pais

nossos ídolos
ainda são os mesmos
e as aparências, as aparências
não enganam, não
você diz que depois deles
não apareceu mais ninguém

você pode até dizer
que eu estou por fora
ou então
que eu estou enganando

mas é você
que ama o passado
e que não vê
é você
que ama o passado
e que não vê
que o novo sempre vem

e hoje eu sei, eu sei
que quem me deu a ideia
de uma nova consciência
e juventude
está em casa
guardado por deus
contando o seus metais

minha dor é perceber
que apesar de termos
feito tudo, tudo, tudo
tudo o que fizemos
ainda somos
os mesmos e vivemos
ainda somos
os mesmos e vivemos
ainda somos
os mesmos e vivemos
como os nossos pais

simplesmente belchior! sejamos capitães de nossas almas não importando qual a sentença dizia um crítico inglês.
 #poemas#world#brasil#jovens#freiheit#liberdade#vida#life#linguaportuguesa#belchior#viveravida#abujamra#filosofia#univers

text:
here is another type of before and after pic i am sharing with permission from my rehab roomie @wilsonme16 
in the before picture mallory was 7 months sober and the after is the result of a 5 day binge. it's amazing to see how much damage can be caused by alcohol in such a short time and how quickly one drink leads to another. 
when i moved from in patient treatment in malibu to sober living in santa monica i was incredibly nervous about the roommate situation but didn't have money for a private room so when i met mallory i almost died from happiness! a single woman close to my age with no kids from the midwest! we quickly became like peas in a pod and had such a wonderful experience together. 
we were super into working out, getting our steps in and hitting up various places to hike and eat greek frozen yogurt .  we went to aa meetings all over the city and mallory made the experience sooo memorable and fun. 
sadly our lives took incredibly different paths since leaving santa monica and my sweet roommate has been in the battle of her life to stay sober. she has gotten to 8.5 months in the past but is committed to finding long term sobriety. 
she wanted me to share this to help someone else who is struggling and let them know that they are not alone. mallory's experience is far more typical than mine, most people relapse many times and we need to be more understanding that it doesn't matter how many times you fall back, the most important thing is that you get up and try again. 
keep my roomie in your thoughts and hopefully this will help someone struggling today!

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the start.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit the hijacked party of puppets is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the bombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on my bed.

the whole qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is obvious that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing for the 2016 election.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are just helpless with the content and more or less fake accounts - there is no way they are going to risk their business by taking the responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole thing is build on the same user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

and here comes the best part. trumq is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words.

the bigger issue still is that requqlicans are willingly piggybacking this lunacy and abusing the faith of their fellow men while campaigning for the midterms. this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

a non

together, we can rise above violence!

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the start.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit the hijacked party of puppets is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the bombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on my bed.

the whole qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is obvious that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing for the 2016 election.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are just helpless with the content and more or less fake accounts - there is no way they are going to risk their business by taking the responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole thing is build on the same user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

and here comes the best part. trumq is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words.

the bigger issue still is that requqlicans are willingly piggybacking this lunacy and abusing the faith of their fellow men while campaigning for the midterms. this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

a non

text:
what a fantastic take on measure for measure we caught tonight at donmar warehouse. the acting was surely great but that wasn't even the best aapect. the real treat was the concept itself. the roles of the abuser and the abused, angelo and isabel, are reverted. we see the whole story once, as intended, and in period costume. then a second time with the gender swap. first of all: william knew what he was doing and even centuries later those lines resonate tremendously, particularly now with #metoo. but the most fascinating realisation is that isabel is always the victim and actually she ends up being even more so when she was the one in power. there's a clear and unsettling connection between patriarchy and power and the play exacerbates how roles and unbalances are forced on us. a thoroughly great creation. kudos to the whole cast and much love to our queen @wellhayley
..
.

text:
i saved the best for last! #applecrisp is hands down my favorite dessert! like ... ever. 🍎
.
you combine oatmeal, one of my favorite foods, with apples and all the autumn spices and it’s a-mazing! top it off with some vanilla ice cream of choice and you can not go wrong. this dessert is fast, easy and delicious #asoulsurvivordesserts 😋.
.
- 3 large granny smith apples (415 g)
- 1/4 cup water
- 1 tbsp. lemon juice
- 1 tbsp. corn starch
- 3/4 cup brown sugar
- 1/2 cup flour
- 1/2 cup old fashion oats
- 5 tbsp. butter, softened
- 2 tsp. cinnamon
- 1/2 tsp. nutmeg
.
1. set oven to 350
2. cut and peel the apples into slices and place in the bottom of a 8x8 pan. 
3. combine water, lemon juice and cornstarch and pour over apples. 
4. in a separate mixing bowl combine brown sugar, flour, oats, butter, cinnamon and nutmeg and - using a pastry blender or fork - cut the butter into the mixture until it crumbles. 
5. pour the butter and oatmeal mixture over the apples and bake 30-45 minutes until it bubbles.
.
serves 4 
calories: 426 
c: 72.3 f:14.8 p:2.9

.

.

-link to article below-

when the average person hears the word "rape," they only think of a man attacking a woman. many people don't know male victims exist. the same goes for the topics of domestic violence and child molestation. one might say, "well that's because men don't speak up.

oh, men are speaking up. then they get shut down by laughter, shaming tactics, and accusations of lying for attention. governments refuse to fund shelters for abused men, police and crisis centers turn them away, and just giving them a voice is somehow considered offensive. hell, there used to be a facebook group whose members would laugh and share stories about abusing their men. that group flew under the radar for months, attracting 200,000+ members!

i've written about these cover-ups on the blog. you can learn more about them by visiting the following link.

www.phenomenalact.com/single-post/afraid-support

text_retweet:
this is the kind of reminder i need in a flashback #allsurvivorsday #repost @theempoweredtherapist with @get_repost
・・・
the impact of trauma can be intense and long lasting. healing from trauma may mean intensive and long-term treatment, as the impact trauma has on memory, the body, and the nervous system, can be profound⠀
💜⠀
trauma memories have a big impact on survivors’ explicit and implicit memory. trauma can shut down parts of memory, can cause survivors to be triggered without explanation, and can change patterns in procedural memory⠀
💜⠀
all of these memory related shifts can lead to increased dissociation, and unwanted somatic experiences that may be unexplained. the body may feel pain or numbness as a response to a trauma trigger, and since the survivor’s brain is off line (during dissociation) they may lack the context for what is happening. here, the mind, body, and nervous system are trapped in the trauma memory ⠀
💜⠀
in these moments, it often feels like your body is betraying you, and you may feel increased distress which could make way for feelings of guilt or shame⠀
💜⠀
this process may be circular, and it may take trauma-informed therapy (and other trauma-informed treatments) to get the mind, body, and nervous system, all on the same page. don’t give up on your healing, with increased awareness and self-acceptance, you will learn to cope with your trauma in ways that are in service of your healing 💜⠀
.⠀
#trauma #traumaaware #traumainformed #traumatherapy #traumatherapist #recovery #healing #thebodykeepsthescore #heal #survivor #survivors #ptsd #cptsd #memory #traumamemories #emdr #somaticexperiencing #psychology #counseling #empower #empowered #selfacceptance #selfcare #mentalhealth #metoo #theempoweredtherapist

умение признавать свою неправоту - хорошее качество. раньше мое мнение было немного иным. по данному вопросу. 
намедни (после инцидента в уфе) общались с друзьями на тему херассмента. ну, или по-русски - домогательств. конечно, ситуация вокруг этой темы на западе - гипертрофированна. но здесь, в россии, защите женщин и мужчин уделяется очень мало внимания. примерно...🤔 примерно нисколько. кому звонить? куда обращаться? в полицию? да у нас человека убивать будут, она приедет через несколько часов! максимум - пообещают провести проверку. на деле - все заявления уходят в стол или шредер.

чего стоит только ситуация с тремя полицейскими и их коллегой! почему нужно это выносить на суд общественности и правоохранителей только в таких крайних мерах, пока дело не дойдёт до физического насилия?! вы знаете в крае хоть одну правозащитную организацию, которая занималась бы этим вопросом? а в стране в общем? а представительство ее? нет. терпи. и все. все так у нас в россии. хочешь жить? терпи. хочешь работать? терпи. хочешь спокойствия? терпи. даже чтобы сохранить репутацию - надо терпеть, и что!! порой даже в голову не укладывается, что бывает за закрытой дверью! когда-нибудь здесь, в нашей стране, оценят по достоинству человеческую жизнь, права и свободы. и полетят... #мысливслух

do y’all hear me? there is a better way for you. it’s not the only way, sure, but let me promise you it’s an effective, safe and sustainable way to show up as the best version of yourself.
.
so, get in your superwoman stance ((as pictured)) and let’s do these hard things together until they aren’t that hard anymore 😘

text:
with the #metoo campaign currently going around, i feel like i need to share something. if you are a survivor of childhood sexual abuse, there is something you can do to help you on your journey to heal. 
the younique foundation offers a free retreat to survivors of childhood sexual abuse. they don't force younique products on you, they don't even use our products in the makeover and photoshoot because they don't want there to be even an ounce of room for someone to say they have the wrong intentions. this foundation has one purpose, and one purpose only: to help you heal. 
no business. no sales. nothing except opportunities for you to rediscover your self-worth and heal. you are powerful beyond measure. 
if you want to know more, please check out www.youniquefoundation.org, where you can read more and apply to attend the retreat or contact me. 
#nomore1in4 #reclaimhope  #ibelieveyou

text:
excerpt from my new piece up at hyperallergic: written after the kavanaugh hearing, a rallying cry. #kavanaugh #metoo “it is time to collect all memories of violence living in our bodies… the heart-pounding footsteps approaching behind us, the “accidental” brushing against our breasts, the muttered-under-the breath vulgarities, the cat-called threats, the porn-induced fantasies, the subway erections, the casting couches, the ogling bosses, the lecherous uncles, the pinches, the tweaks, the grabs, the unwanted kisses, the pinning against walls, the reminders that they are stronger (and they could do it, even if they didn’t), the ones-we-thought-were-friends who did not “stop,” the monsters who came out of nowhere to take what they wanted, the ones who laughed at our helplessness as they held us down, the ones who took turns with our bodies, and the ones who killed us, or left us for dead.

these traumas never go away. they only intensify with the slow realization that it is now our daughters’ turn to live through this unending nightmare of male violence...”. kate kretz, “une femme d’un certain âge (a woman of a certain age)” (2014, detail), grey hair of many women, hand embroidered on black cotton, 33 x 22 inches, james swope and scott robertson collection, west palm beach, florida (photo by greg staley, image courtesy the artist). link:  https://hyperallergic.com/469146/the-momentum-of-this-moment-kate-kretz/?fbclid=iwar0axqmezlwafsu19gljgpnbzef8cdoy2bvh1jmpxos88_uclxwkwjdqaqi

text:
the online modelpreneur bootcamp is about to launch!! the bootcamp will teach models of all levels some of the tools, tips and tricks to help them maneuver through this industry as a self represented model. they will learn both how to find an agency and how to work without one, among other things. the online bootcamp is open to models of all ages worldwide!
•
as for the expedition, we’ve recently partnered with a paris fashion week show to be able to create a career changing opportunity for aspiring, established, and freelance models both male and female! the international modelpreneur expedition will be open to all types of fashion creatives (photographers, mua, hairstylists, designers, etc) that are looking to enhance, start, or further their career and portfolio! we will be taking paris fashion week by storm, together! there will be limited spots available for this so please be sure to subscribe on the site for updates on how you can join the modelpreneur crew on our international expedition to paris fashion week. for more information on all of the amazing benefits that the course and expedition have to offer head to the site! link in bio 😊

fy fan för den man som stal min trygghet och försökte förvägra mig min rätt till liv.
fy fan för honom som fortfarande hemsöker mig.
och fy fan för det destruktiva patriarkatet som gör att jag inte är ensam. #metoo

text:
she wants to speak up
but writing is the only way she knows
that’s how she expresses herself best
they tell her,
don’t speak up
a girl’s tongue should be locked in her mouth
why?
didn’t your mother teach you not to touch what doesn’t belong to you?
or is it your father?
he certainly didn’t teach you how to be a man enough
it must be so
lose weight 
your ass is too appealing
gain weight
your ass is still too appealing 
show up
you’re too attractive
cover up
you make him curious
never care
never listen
you are not alone
it happened before
it happens now
it will happen
and keep happening
it’s not your fault
you are strong
you are powerful
you have a tongue that would bury him into the depths of earth
can’t you see his fearful eyes when you blew your fire at him?
don’t ever be afraid
fear is created to cripple perverts like him
so fuck him and fuck who are like him
i know touching your ass reminded you
of that young girl who thought she’d get pregnant because her breast was grabbed
but little did she know
you felt sorry for her
no one was there to tell her the truth
to redeem her
she struggled
but she moved on
you’re a woman now
still, that girl can’t leave your mind
a hand on her breast
a touch on your ass
these things don’t define you
they define how filthy their hands are
you have a tongue that can’t be silent 
you have a roar of a lioness
fire of dragon
so use them
they are your weapon
speak up
you don’t have the right to
you let him do it
you didn’t yell at him
you accepted this
it will always be your mistake
you will always be blamed
so why stay silent?
it’s a male-dominated society
they’ll blame it all on me
it’s a female-populated society
we’ll crush them under our bathroom slippers
let them hear your voice
sing your story
let them hear your melodies
put down that pen and paper
they won’t read
they will listen
mesmerize them with your bravery and the bitterness of your tongue
i’m here for you
let me hold your hand while you let go of that burden on your chest
say it out loud
speak aloud
you don’t need no microphone 
for your mouth is meant to be a megaphone!

text:
——— m i n d s e t ———
.
when we work on our health we must do it from all aspects of our health. this all includes mind, spirit, and of course body. working from the inside out is always a great way to begin your health journey. .
oh people are watching me...
oh people are going to make fun of me...
oh my abdomen is jiggling to much...
oh my should just stay in head...
oh people love me this way...
oh i’m already here why change it...
oh it’s cold out now...
oh it’s to hot out...
oh my clothing is not good for working out...
oh all the sweat...
oh i don’t have space to workout...
oh i can’t afford a gym membership...
oh i can’t afford those quick fix pills...
oh i can’t afford a trainer...
oh i can’t ...... you can’t what?!
i use those excuses but others looking at me and giving their opinion of me or at least what my crazy thought are building up in there is not real.
.
you yourself is the only one building all that garbage. you start changing those words wow the possibilities are freak’n endless! 
i say this because i had all those thoughts. they creep up here and there.
i have had thoughts of being better of dead but i have yeld ao loud to be quiet!! told myself while yelling at myself who the heck will that benefit? 
you? 
your children? 
your parents? 
your family? 
nah! no one! 
not even those who have hurt you. 
yup they are part of the mix. why? because you would be doing it for them. may not make sense to you but it makes sense. you only need to wake up and remember you we’re created with a freak’n purpose that only you can bring forth. those words may sound like a broken record player on replay but it’s freak’n truth!
.
so you may not “feel like it” but get up and move. this stimulated your mind body and spirit to keep pushing. all the right hormone will start reigniting.
.
this is my story and i chose to breath everyday for me!
.

text_retweet: i am a victim of abuse. i am processing a lot of #trauma these days. i’m amazed at how, with every epiphany, i realize that “they” were all right. a lot of my pain has been self created. not by choosing pain, but by choosing the familiar. the tendency to seek out comfort in the familiar feelings, in abusive language, projections and all things toxic, were what i felt home to be. i’m a victim of #abuse i no longer need to wonder what is wrong with me, and why do i always feel this way, and why do people keep saying that to me? and pattern after pattern repeated for god knows how many lifetimes in this one alone. what i’ve done with that, is still my responsibility. how i spend my precious time, where i put my mental, emotional and physical energy. what #no feels like from the world and from my heart. i am learning to hear and say no! i am a victim of abuse. what i choose to do with that is my fucking #choice  image repost from @thewildfeminine #metoo #imwithher #noisapowerfulword

text: this is america!!! this is the original hand picked “complexions” company full of original artists each with gifts beyond compare. dwight and desmond never looked at the color of our skin they looked at our hearts and the passion we held in them. we came from all different companies, training and countries. no one, nobody had ever created anything like this! we weren’t sure anyone would come to that first performance on that humid spring night in new york at symphony space. but they did and the company gave every inch of their souls and laid them out on the stage for everyone to see. the audience nearly tore the theatre apart!!! it was the most electrifying, incredible experience of my life. i will never be able to thank dwight and desmond for giving this small town dancer a chance and i will never be able to the thank the artists i shared the stage with. they made me better by just standing next to me. this is why this country exists. freedom to do, express and love freely. “e pluribus unum,” out of many, one. please remember this image this tuesday and please vote with the deepest part of your heart.  please. 🙏🏻 #vote #dancers #dance #ballet #complexionscontemporaryballet #contemporarydance  #hiphop #blacklivesmatter #weshallovercome #metoo  #believe #america #nyc #rockthevote

text:
~ • n e i n • ~
ich frage mich immer wieder, warum es manchen menschen so verdammt schwer fällt ein nein zu akzeptieren! damit meine ich nicht meinen fast zweijährigen, der nicht in die waschmaschine klettern darf. nein. ich meine erwachsene, die einem eine frage stellen und die antwort ignorieren. die vor einer tat fragen und es trotzdem machen, egal wie die antwort lautet. eltern, die ihre kinder etwas fragen und ein klares nein dennoch ignorieren. •
wozu fragen die leute überhaupt? wozu mache ich mir die mühe eine nette, negative antwort zu formulieren, wenn ich doch genau weiß, dass sie sowieso ignoriert wird. •
wieso kann man nicht einfach akzeptieren, was andere menschen wollen oder eben gerade nicht wollen! egal ob baby, das nicht abgelegt werden will. kleinkind, dass nicht alleine als erstes einen raum voller fremder menschen betreten will. ein erwachsener, der nicht umarmt oder angefasst werden will. •
akzeptiert einfach die grenzen anderer! lasst die menschen in ruhe wenn sie es wollen! gebt ihnen was sie brauchen, wenn ihr genau das gerade geben könnt. gebt sicherheit, ohne aufdringlich zu sein oder bloß zu stellen. seid einfach da und vor allem aufmerksam auf die bedürfnisse anderer! gerade für die menschen die ihr liebt, lieb habt oder beschützen wollt. •
#nein #neinheisstnein #metoomovement #metoo #aufmerksamkeit #selbstbestimmt #geborgenwachsen #geborgenheit #ruhe #kindheit #meinkörpergehörtmir

text: i know i’m pretty late with posting this, but at the time of the movement’s popularity i just wasn’t ready. i wanted to post this now because my therapist and i have both agreed that it is a very important step in my recovery from the negative effects i still face. that’s what they always tell us the first step to recovery is, don’t they? admitting there’s a problem. i’m posting this because i need to for me. and because when i was too scared to speak up, other women’s posts encouraged me and helped me feel like i was not alone and was not the things i heard people around me say about survivors. and as much as posting this will help me continue to get better, i know it will help others too who feel the way i did. i won’t give a name or details, those are things i’m choosing to keep private. but i wanted to stop hiding. to stop being ashamed. this is part of my story. for years i didn’t want to say that it was. so now, given strength by other women and by the case of dr. ford and her courage, i can say #metoo. because what happened to me is as likely as rain. and the moment we stop hiding is the moment that change begins to happen. i know some of you will disagree with my choice to post this. and that’s okay. this isn’t for you. it’s for me. 💛

flashback
 hollywood's biggest night took time to deliver a timely message and celebrate diversity in filmmaking; 
ashley judd, salma hayek and annabella sciorra — three women who publicly accused harvey weinstein of sexual misconduct — took the stage together to introduce the segment.

when jimmy kimmel kicked off this year's oscars, he promised a "night of positivity" during his opening monologue. during the third act of sunday's show, that promise materialized when the academy devoted a segment to honoring the  and time's up movements and highlighted the diversity in movie-making in the last year. "many spoke their truth and the journey ahead is long, but slowly a new path has emerged," said judd, referencing the women and men who have come forward to say  and time's up. those voices have joined together to create a "mighty chorus," she added. judd shared a hope that the next 90 years of the academy awards will "empower these limitless possibilities of equality, diversity inclusivity, intersectionality — that's what this year has promised us." hayek then introduced a pre-taped segment highlighting some of this year's most diverse and ground-breaking filmmakers — from greta gerwig and dee rees to  duvernay and kumail jiani — whom she referred to as "unstoppable spirits who kicked ass and broke through bias perceptions against their gender racer and ethnicity to tell their stories." jimmy kimmel said : "we need to set an example and if we can work together here to stop sexual harassment in the workplace, women will only have to deal with harassment all the time, at every other place they go." perhaps speaking to critics of hollywood award shows who believe they have grown "too political," kimmel explained that the night's show would include brave and outspoken voices of the   and  movements in hopes of spurring positive change. "this is a night for positivity," he declared before rattling off all the names of nominees who had the potential to break or set new records if they were to win.

    &  take the stage at the

text:
who is the "tiger girl"? for her first new york exhibition, emi katsuta was inspired to create a work in the wake of the #metoo movement as an homage to women's strength and courage. as part of her artist's statement about the work katsuta wrote that "these days, the #metoomovement continues to stir things up and a number of strong female figures have emerged. these tough, powerful tigers have for too long been trapped in a cute frame, unable to sound their full roar. it's a situation we've all grown to accept. this time is different. it's okay to be strong, it's okay to show that strength. so, let me hear you roar! the time has come!" .
.
.
.
see tiger girl and emi katsuta's other recent works in emi katsuta: that fantastic someone on view at seizan gallery ny through january 5, 2019 photo by @gionstudio

text:
#100happydays day 20: i can say with certainty that i owe my life to this little device. my alpha-stim helped break the beta wave block in my brain caused by complex trauma. after my first session, i told the therapist, “am i ok to drive? i feel so calm...” she replied, “you are fine to drive! that is simply the brainwaves that calm you down, kickstarted and working again...has it been awhile since you’ve felt that?” “yes...i think i was maybe 16?” (this coincides with my first sexual assault) 
i now use alpha stim daily, and it has helped me wean off of benzos for panic, and helped build up the alpha waves in my brain so i can react with calmness to stress again - something that was a huge struggle for decades. 
help is out there. also...this is not a fucking ad. i bought this, and it’s helped so much. 
#survivor #metoo #ptsd #depression #anxiery #agoraphobia #alphastim

text:
one of my councillors suggested i try meditation. i thought this was absolutely ridiculous and that it was in no way going to help me. though, i figured i’d take a professionals suggestion and try it. 
there are many misconceptions with meditation people think you need to clear your mind, when in fact meditation is being aware of your thoughts, where you are, and how you’re feeling. coming in touch with yourself. i’m not going to lie sometimes my mind wanders to dark places but focusing on my breathing and being in touch with my body has helped to control panic attacks during flashbacks. 
if you have a couple minutes give it a try the results might surprise you. you also don’t need to have experienced a trauma to come in touch with yourself. anyone can try it! #believeinyourvoice .
.
.
.

text:
bird bath 🛀 🐥
(created by: @bad_birdy )
2 oz. (60ml) gin 
1 oz. (30ml) lime juice 
3/4 oz. (22ml) rosemary pomegranate syrup 
2 drops saline 
champagne 
rosemary air 
preparation 
1. in a shaking glass, combine gin, lime juice, rosemary pomegranate syrup, and saline. add ice and shake well. 
2. strain mix into serving glass and top with champagne 
3. to create rosemary air, steep rosemary in 500 grams of water for 4 minutes. add a sheet of gelatin and allow it to bloom for 10 mins. stir in pot until gelatin has dissolved. add a dab of xantham gum and shake mixture. 
4. using an air pump, create bubbles in the rosemary air and scoop them onto the serving glass. 
5. garnish with a rubber duck and enjoy responsibly!  #amazing #fantastic #good #yummy #delicious #tasty #love #handmade #video #likeforfollow #instadrink #instagood #instacocktails #infused #mixologist #mixology #cocktails🍹 #coctailart #thebest #bestcocktails #bartenderforlife #bartender #biutiful #biutifulday #metoo #barbegov

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text: einen wunderschönen samstag! hier sind wieder eure meinungsmacherinnen, eure göttinnen, eure traumfrauen und traumerfüllerinnen: die #adipositanten ! wir melden uns heute mit einer hommage an multikulturalität, an das leben und an den veganen lifestyle. wie ihr alle wisst, sind wir verfechterinnen des prinzips „küche, kinder, kirche“, keineswegs bedeutet dies jedoch, dass wir uns neuem verschließen. in unserem habitat, der küche, können auch wir mal richtig verrückt werden! als verdeutlichendes beispiel führen wir den heutigen tag an. der november hat begonnen, und somit die jahreszeit, in dem das angebot an regionalem, in plastikfolie eingeschweißtem obst und gemüse stark reduziert ist. um unsere lieben 🥰 gesund durch diese monate zu tragen, müssen wir nichtsdestotrotz für eine geregelte vitaminzufuhr 🥗 🌶 🌽 🥒 🥙 sorgen. aus diesem grund gab es heute, inspiriert von @gustavgruenms (werbung wegen markennennung) eine komposition aus salat, falafel und weizentortilla. ein voller erfolg! dazu gab es frisch gebrühten tee aus asiatischen kräutern, die von eseln nach mitteleuropa getragen wurden, um emissionen zu vermeiden! also: heute gab es nahrungsmittel aus vieler herren länder, die uns alle näher zusammengebracht haben. in der vorweihnachtszeit fordern wir: liebe! liebt einander, liebt euren nächsten! liebt den nachbarn mit migrantenhintergrund! seid offen und tolerant. wir versuchen, euch ein beispiel zu sein! einen wunderschönen, inspirierten und erfüllten abend wünschen eure #adipositanten
name: die Adipositanten
tweet_full: einen wunderschönen samstag! hier sind wieder eure meinungsmacherinnen, eure göttinnen, eure traumfrauen und traumerfüllerinnen: die #adipositanten ! wir melden uns heute mit einer hommage an multikulturalität, an das leben und an den veganen lifestyle. wie ihr alle wisst, sind wir verfechterinnen des prinzips „küche, kinder, kirche“, keineswegs bedeutet dies jedoch, dass wir uns neuem verschließen. in unserem habitat, der küche, können auch wir mal richtig verrückt werden! als verdeutlichendes beispiel führen wir den heutigen tag an. der november hat begonnen, und somit die jahreszeit, in dem das angebot an regionalem, in plastikfolie eingeschweißtem obst und gemüse stark reduziert ist. um unsere lieben 🥰 gesund durch diese monate zu tragen, müssen wir nichtsdestotrotz für eine geregelte vitaminzufuhr 🥗 🌶 🌽 🥒 🥙 sorgen. aus diesem grund gab es heute, inspiriert von @gustavgruenms (werbung wegen markennennung) eine komposition aus salat, falafel und weizentortilla. ein voller erfolg! dazu gab es frisch gebrühten tee aus asiatischen kräutern, die von eseln nach mitteleuropa getragen wurden, um emissionen zu vermeiden! also: heute gab es nahrungsmittel aus vieler herren länder, die uns alle näher zusammengebracht haben. in der vorweihnachtszeit fordern wir: liebe! liebt eider, liebt euren nächsten! liebt den nachbarn mit migrantenhintergrund! seid offen und tolerant. wir versuchen, euch ein beispiel zu sein! einen wunderschönen, inspirierten und erfüllten abend wünschen eure #adipositanten

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
smc mbb team statement
(swipe for full statement) **please share** we, the 13 members of the saint michael's college men's basketball team, want to take this opportunity to continue the discussion we started when we took a knee before the game between our two teams last year. 
the injustices we protested against by kneeling last year continue to this day. so does the need for protest against those injustices. we kneel to highlight the daily prejudices faced by african americans, simply due to the color of their skin.

but tonight we also join in solidarity with our jewish brothers and sisters fighting anti-semitism and our muslim friends fighting islamophobia. we protest to support those impacted by the #metoo movement, those in the lgbtq+ community and in addition we speak out against the unjust treatment of homeless and rejected veterans, and any american who has felt the sting of injustice, prejudice and discrimination. 
we want to be clear that our protest and the act of kneeling has nothing to do with the flag or the military. we love our country and that is why we kneel. dissent is patriotic! we owe it to those who are marginalized and excluded to speak out in the face of injustice. we kneel because of a desire to improve our country. we want to ensure that all are included when we speak of "liberty & justice for all!"

the bigger issue still is that requqlicans are willingly piggybacking this lunacy and abusing the faith of their fellow men while campaigning for the midterms. this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
yesterday morning, november 2nd my sister elisabet passed away. as many of you know, she meant the world to me. her life was a a true example of perseverance, passion, elegance and unconditional love.
my bond to my oldest sister started early in life when she took care of me as a child. as i became an adult she taught me so many valuable lessons imprinted in my soul that made the person i am today. my heart is broken. my best friend, sister, confident, mentor and mother figure has left to be part of eternity.
her passion to educate women in the corporate world to stand for themselves inspired many all over the world. she spoke on women’s right in brazil, prague and all over the us bringing hope and awareness of how to work in an environment way before the #metoo movement. she inspired everyone she touched. an amazing mother and wife. a role model to her siblings and a loving daughter.
funny and loud! always had a story to tell and every single time she entered a room her inner light and physical beauty shined like a star. there will be a service in pittsburgh next week and the following week she will have a service and will be buried in her puerto rico. once i have more information i will be sure to posted.
i am so honored and blessed to have had the experience of having such powerful relationship in my life. 
i love you beba and will think of you every day of my life.

text:
bojack horseman is an animated series for adults, created by raphael bob-waksberg with the voices of will arnett, amy sedaris, alison brie, paul f. tompkins, and aaron paul. "1990s sitcom star bojack horseman is now a has-been with no love life and a permanent house guest. then he gets a book deal -- and a cute ghostwriter." this is how the series kicks off and from that point on there's no horsing around since each season brings great laughs, good drama, social commentary, and psychological journeys. - -

bojack horseman season 5 is an apt follow up to the 4 outstanding seasons that came before it. it weaves in real world issues such as #metoo and the industry scene in "hollywoo". it continues to dig into complicated family ties, relationships, and friendships and to explore sex, drugs, alcohol, anxiety. depression, and a deluge of surprising things. the script is as witty as ever. it's dark and disturbing and yet incredibly funny and sharply humorous. this may well be netfilx's best series to date. it's already won several well-deserved awards... and we can't wait for season 6. post by the movie buff critic @jasminanajjar -
-

text:
last evening at the mall, as i flipped through a book of colourful labels,
i looked up, only to find an unfamiliar crowd around me.
oh no! i had lost sight of mom again.
taking one last look, i abandoned the book,
and set out in search of her.
she had to be in the vegetable section, or maybe upstairs picking out a shirt for dad's birthday?
i zigzaged through strangers with my mind alert for straight brown hair and a saffron kurthi. 
it was 15 minutes later, that i bumped into him.
tall, dark and ugly; with disheveled hair and a black t-shirt.
not exactly my current priority, i muttered a distracted sorry and walked ahead.
frustrated, at not being able to find mom,
i quicked my steps,
only to bump into someone again, harder this time.
the same black shirt and ugly face.
mentally registering this, to make sure it didn't happen again,
i hurried away, embarassed. 
i reached upstairs, and debated if i should search for a help desk; something that mom told me existed to help lost children.
i slammed into someone again, 
sending a shooting pain through the front of my chest. 
shocked, i looked up to a familiar ugly face,
with a yellow smile, that was anything but apologetic. 
i couldn't tell what was louder at that point of time - the buzzing crowd around me or the alarms that went off in my head. 
recoiling from his presence, i tried to dodge past,
and before i could anticipate, his hand reached forwards to grab on to me. 
pain was a secondary issue,
as disgust, anger and fear made themselves clearly apparent. 
running now, i desperately looked for someone trustworthy.
only to panic, on seeing his familiar shirt behind me,
following me through the crowd. 
it was a half-hour long dangerous hide and seek, three more immoral bumpings, and a horrendous instance of seeing him touch himself later, before i lost him.
and found myself staring at a lady wearing saffron, standing next to a desk; 
making frantic gestures to a salesman, who tried to calm her down. 
my story of an indian 10 year old; her story of a pakistani infant girl; their story of an american 25 year old woman. 
five letters that we had in common. 
#metoo

#women #society #trending #bold #gender #empowering

text:
aloe vera gelly 
الو فيرا جيلي ( 85%الوفيرا ) 
منذ القدم استعملت نبتة الالوة لمعالجة الحروق الطفيفة وتضميد الجروح باستخلاص اللب من اوراقها اما اليوم 
فقد اصبحت في متناول يدك في منتج الوفيرا جيلي فهو عباره عن جل سميك به مواد مرطبة تدهن به البشره لبلسمتها وتكييفها تمتصه البشره كليا فلا يترك اثار بقع على الملابس ذو مفعول ممتاز على الحروق الطفيفة حب الشباب ، الاكزيما ، والحساسية الجلدية حيث اجريت عدة دراسات على 60 من المصابين بمشاكل جلدية وكانت 
النتائج مبهره واثبتت ان 80% منهم انتفعوا ولم تلاحظ عليهم اي اثار جانبية ، يخفف الحكة والتورم والقرح كما ساعد مفعوله المضاد للجراثيم في محاربة الالتهابات كما يفيد في التقرحات الجلدية في الاماكن الحساسة ويساعد على تخفيف التهيجات له مفعول ممتاز في حالة التعرض لعلاج اشعاعي كما تستخدم الكوفيرات والحلاقين على منابت الشعر قبل تجعيد او صبغ الشعر لحماية البشرة 
السعة: 120مل 
طريقة الاستعمال : 
تنظف البشرة جيدا قبل دهنها ويكرر الدهن قدر الحاجة 
الفوائد والمزايا الرئيسية : 
_ اسعاف اولي لكافة المشاكل الجلدية ( حب الشباب , اكزيما, التهاب جلد , حروق النار والشمس ) 
_ مفيد للكدمات والدمامل والتقرحات والفطريات 
_ ذو فعالية جيدة لمشاكل الانف والفم#كلنا_ثقه_في_محمد_بن_سلمان #لازما_العايل_زمينا #السعودية_العظمى #تصريح #metoo #السعودية

text:
so, yesterday, i was standing in a crowded place with some random girl whose bra strap was showing. okay i know its normal. i know every girl wears it. i know there's nothing to be hushed about or stare at.
but my concern was if i should tell her or stay silent.! for the very first time i found this thought strange. i'll tell you why!
nowadays feminists and their feminism has made this "bra strap is normal" soooo famous and *abnormal* that i wasn't really sure how would that girl react. i don't know if she too was a fake feminist or just another girl who would not want her bra strap showing. i wasn't sure if she would thank me or slap me. i wasn't sure if i would be doing a favour or insulting yet another woman and feminism.
i know bras are totally a normal thing, i too wear one. but don't you think these "bras are normal" have actually made this more of an issue now? i mean what do you want us to do? to hide it or show it off? i know its a woman's personal choice. but should i tell her or let her be? and if i let her be, do you think she, too, is a strong, independent, confident girl who would not mind her strap being out in public. i know its normal but i don't think every girl would be comfortable with it. then what should we do???
and thus, fake feminism not just made it difficult to decide but rather made it more difficult to reach out other women! and in a situation of talking to that girl, i was too scared to approach her..
📸and✍️ @couthy_vibes
.
.
.

text:
‘passionate berry’
.
you will need:
30ml blanco tequila 
30ml passionfruit liqueur 
60ml @thejuice_lab berry goodness*
15ml lemon juice

simply place all ingredients in a cocktail shaker and shake vigorously until combined. double strain into your favourite cocktail glass. garnish with freshly frozen blackberries and finely sliced mint.
.
* berry goodness is made with pear, apple, coconut water, blueberry, boysenberry, and raspberry.

text: triggers are real, and in many cases misunderstood. when a survivor experiences a trigger/episode, they loose track of their surrounding, and “relive” a particular traumatic event they. in this case, the survivor continuously lives with fear, and would rather die, cause self harm, use drugs to escape their pain, rather than continue to relive the pain triggers, and their past abuse causes over and over again. learning about triggers, and their effects will help you better support your child, or loved one who is a survivor. #buddyspeaks #metoo #endchildhoodsexualabuse #trauma #emotionaltrauma #boys #girls #survivors #pain #knife #mentalhealth #life #survivor #endthestigma #ptsd #depression #abuse #selfharm #suicidal #therapy #recovery #csaqt #stopabuse #children

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
tieni sempre presente che la pelle fa le rughe, i capelli diventano bianchi, i giorni si trasformano in anni.
però ciò che é importante non cambia; la tua forza e la tua convinzione non hanno età. il tuo spirito è la colla di qualsiasi tela di ragno.
dietro ogni linea di arrivo c’è una linea di partenza.
dietro ogni successo c’è un`altra delusione.
fino a quando sei viva, sentiti viva.
se ti manca ciò che facevi, torna a farlo.
non vivere di foto ingiallite… insisti anche se tutti si aspettano che abbandoni.
non lasciare che si arrugginisca il ferro che c’è in te.
fai in modo che invece che compassione, ti portino rispetto.
quando a causa degli anni non potrai correre, cammina veloce.
quando non potrai camminare veloce, cammina. quando non potrai camminare, usa il bastone. però non arrenderti mai! #madreteresa #nonmollaremai #breastcancerawareness #breastcancer #vita #cancersurvivor #vita #metoo #leguerrieresciencesartsandevents

text:
jeg har mange gode minner fra tidlig barndom. fine somre hos bestemor i alta. varmen inntil bestemorkroppen, mens vi satt ute på varme trappetrinn, og dyppet rabarbra i sukkerkoppen. sommeren hos henne var alltid et eventyr av frihet. min mor ble kalt dokka, fordi hun er så liten. for oss ble hun til dokkemamma, og vi elsket henne slik kun to småjenter kan. jeg husker det iskalde huset i blåsenborgveien, der vi bodde det første året i hammerfest. selv om vi frøs på vinteren hadde vi det koselig, og hun gjorde så godt hun kunne som skilt alenemamma til to jenter med forskjellig far. på 60-tallet var akkurat det en evig kamp mot bygdedyret. men jeg husker også sinnet hennes. hun kunne bli så sint at vi gikk på nåler for å prøve og være usynlige. vi måtte alltid være på vakt og tilpasse oss hennes humørsvingninger. etter hvert flyttet dokkemammas «store kjærlighet» inn sammen med oss. en mann som hun elsket høyere enn oss barna, en mann med fin uniform og blanke knapper, og som det senere skulle vise seg likte svært unge jenter. hvorfor forteller jeg dette her på instagram, hvor de «vellykkede» speiler sine sprettrumper, og «selger» barna sine for gratis barnevogner? jo, fordi vi alle må bli flinkere å se hva som ligger bak fasadene! bry oss om de mennesken vi har rundt oss. lytte til barna, og tro på barna. for det mest vanlige er ikke å lyve om overgrep, men å tie om det ❤️ jeg mener at alle barn må få lov til å eie seg selv, og sin egen historie, også i sosiale media. når vi i dag vet hvor kort veien kan være fra lettkledde lekende barn i strandkanten, til det samme bildet forsvinner ut på det mørke nettet, bør vi som voksne tenke oss om mange ganger. mange bloggere går i tillegg forran og bruker barna som «tilbehør» de tjener store penger på. barn har ikke evnen til å se konsekvensene, men det bør mor og far gjøre... hva mener du?
.
