abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit the hijacked party of puppets is obviously just business as usual.

the whole qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is obvious that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing for the 2016 election.

the bigger issue still is that requqlicans are willingly piggybacking this lunacy and abusing the faith of their fellow men while campaigning for the midterms. this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
happy halloween 🎃 2018
choosing to portray the goddess m.m
as not just the breathless, blonde explosion of sexiness that people perceived her to be
but also, the tortured marilyn. 
the intelligent, shy, broken, often abused, vulnerable woman - who lacked confidence and self love. the woman who surprised men, when they got to know her personally; that she was far from what she appeared to be on screen. the woman who craved love and reassurance..
gone far too soon.
it is important to remember she was human too.. ❤

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
💰 💴 you see a japanese buddhist monk standing here with his hand held out perfectly straight asking for an offering of money. 💰a donation for the temple.  the buddhist monk will pray over you if you put a donation in his bowl. :
:
🏠🏠🏠
all over the world we can see a person, somewhere,  with their hands held out asking for money. they could be homeless.  they could be without food. actually, more and more people are facing homelessness and housing problems.
:
:
🏠🏠🏠
vincent van gogh said “to save a life is a real and beautiful thing. to make a home for the homeless, yes, it is a thing that must be good; whatever the world may say, it cannot be wrong.”
:
:
🏠🏠🏠
“poverty is the mother of crime.” a quote of marcus aurelius :
:

yes, perhaps we may not completely wipe out the problem of homeless of a family, children, women or men... or to feed the starving in the streets.
...but surely we can still keep trying to do all we can. :
:
just as i know it is a difficult feat  that i took upon myself to do what i can to eradicate rape crimes and other heinous forms of violence committed, but we still move forward. :
:
i have met other warriors on instagram and facebook who have visions of improving the lives of others, somehow or in some way.
:
:
sometimes we have no idea how we will manage to do what we do, but we do know for sure that we will succeed, come rain or shine. :
:
and if we fall, we will just pick ourselves up and just keep going. :
:
as for myself, my grassroots advocacy in japan for almost the past two decades in this movement to eradicate rape and murder, i almost died of exhaustion last year in the process. still in recovery phase at the moment but you can see from the smile on my face that nothing can stop this aussie gal and empowering lives in my life on this earth, will always be my joy.
:
:
to all of my instagram friends who are also on this journey but perhaps with different themes to what i do, i pray for your success and speed in doing so. please do take care of your health on the way as you walk your path, your mission. :
:
in solidarity, 
#catherinejanefisher
you can see our website at [  iamjane . org ]

text:
we are at the culmination of jupiter’s journey in scorpio. 
it was a year of stirring + churning. stimulating trauma + re-traumatizing. 
scorpio action provides the most potent times of transformation. scorpio is the shaman, the alchemist, the phoenix that rises from the ashes. it is a fixed water sign which is interesting because we usually think of the mutable as the transformers but scorpio season wants you to stay in it to feel what your meant to feel. it wants to go beneath the surface of the emotional embodiment. it wants to test your dedication, endurance & commitment to presence no matter what life brings. by staying present, we get to experience the water element in all of its forms. still water, moving water, ice, boiling water. water as it evaporates back up to the clouds + the water that rains down on the earth. always in the state of transformation & every time the water goes through one of these states it changes. it purifies its own form & it changes the landscape. water can also be turbulent like the tides of the ocean or it can be the powerful undertow + the rip current that takes you out that you can only surrender to in order to survive.

once we turn 35 years old, it is much harder to change our ways + beliefs. in brain studies, it shows the fastest way to change a mind is to disrupt it in ways we can’t ignore. the most efficient way to do this is suffering and / or pain. let what you’ve been feeling become the catalyst for your transformation. 
nov 6th, uranus rx moves back into aries season & the north node moves into cancer. 
our nervous systems are going to get amped up again w/ uranus in a fire sign. our purpose points back to our family, our roots, our ancestry. how are we going to take care of each other? show up for each other. interesting that it’s on the same day that we really need to show up at the polls. 
jupiter moves into sagittarius nov 9. everything will shift again. for the better. but we still have work to do. 
the scorpio season astro nidra is up and ready for you. i hope this is the medicine you need to stay connected to your heart. 📷: @thedjpierce

@goblockcon in @vegas was great! i hear... i didn’t have time to attend, but i was honored to help host wcc’s transference dinner at the @palmsplaceluxurysuite 
for those that didn’t come, we missed you! 
would you believe that in this very exclusive event, the only two women in blockchain from  @igkansas found each other, and obviously became bff’s. 😍❤️ you guys will be able to view my content on cryptocentral.io after my team does some heavy editing. 😂 
highlights of the night? i kidnapped all the crypto influencers and took selfies in my penthouse bathroom. (never dome that before. when in vegas?! 😂) the sunset! ❤️❤️❤️❤️ cooking our organic, fresh meal with others that are making huge contributions to blockchain tech. 
making friends with @go_chain & ponder, virtual growth and crypto twitter influencers (they promised to help me learn twitter, thank g-d! 😂) it was lovely. we will be doing a lot more private blockchain events in the future. let me know if you’d like an invite or talk to me about your event and maybe i’ll come film it and bring a few of my crypto friends. ❤️😍😘 -sam

text:
a wonderful piece highlighting the transformation people saw when giving up alcohol.  link in bio!

it's so funny to me now when people say that their drinking isnt an issue and they don't have a problem when i don't drink. i am never the one to bring up the topic, people just like to let me know they don't have a problem 
i say it's funny because it is such an odd reaction and clearly indicates that they do, in fact, have a problem but they can't admit it. people without drinking problems don't need to let me know, they actually don't care about alcohol in any meaningful way and are quite pleasant to be around. i have a few coworkers like this and they have helped me enormously in navigating the required happy hours and drinking focused corporate sales events i attend. 
i wish the other crew could be more open to the potential for even a few months of sobriety or a year. i never say this to them until they have let me know that they do have a problem, which seems to happen in the days and weeks following these corporate events but they never consider soberity as an option 
many men and women have expressed to me that they can't get through the events sober, they can't deal with the stress sober and shut down the entire conversation. it's so sad to hear this because it is not true. it's not easy and doesn't happen overnight but we can do it. 
these limitations are in our head, we can do anything sober and proud. these transformation pics and my own are proof! never give up 💓

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
a lot of you saw my instagram story rant yesterday, but for those of you who didn’t... yesterday as i was crossing the street, a man aggressively grabbed my boob. i was in complete shock and so angry...i turned around, somehow kept myself from punching him in the face, and instead yelled “don’t fucking touch me!” he laughed at me...i was fuming... it felt as if my whole body was on fire and at the same time i wanted to cry. i felt so gross and dirty after that... i walked back to the apartment after ranting on instagram and calling a friend to vent... i wasn’t even wearing anything that was showing off my chest... i was wearing a sweatshirt yesterday but even if i was only wearing my sports bra... it does not matter! it doesn’t matter what i or anyone else is wearing!!! it’s absolutely not an invitation to touch me or anyone else. respect your fellow humans...😪
someone also pointed out to me after my rant... what if i had just had my mastectomy, or just had my reconstruction surgery? he wouldn’t have known, and he could’ve hurt me soooo badly. you don’t know what other people are going through, be kind. keep that in mind. you never know what someone else is going through. 
anywho, something i like to do when i’m upset or having a bad day is taking a shower. it doesn’t matter if i’ve already had one that day... i like hopping in the shower, playing some music, breathing and pressing the restart button. 🌹
p.s. i feel so much better today, thank you so much to everyone who reached out with love.. i appreciate you 🙏🏼
whoever you are who grabbed me yesterday, you can’t take my light. 
it’s here to stay
✨
📸: @morgan.neely1

text: ⏰😡🤬 with just a few days to go before an election that so many americans hope is transformative, i devoured #goodandmad, the new book from the amazing rebecca traister, who has been one of my favorite journalists to read in 2017 and 2018 (and before that, with her thoughtful book #allthesingleladies). traister’s new book explores women’s rage and how it has created change, both historically but more particularly since 2016. one of traister’s gifts as a journalist is her deep empathy for others - her understanding that lots of people are often flawed or could be better or have hurt people without meaning to. she walks through how men have hurt women, how white women have hurt women of color, how rich women have hurt poor women, and how everyone is a little messy. her tone is not uncertain - she is very certain in the power of women’s rage - but rather, it questions assumptions and provides probing analysis that leaves honest room for error, a rare phenomenon in this world where every idiot with a twitter account claims to understand 100% of everyone’s motivations. traister’s book expertly details the #metoo movement, but more than being a primer on the hashtag and rehashing the stories that have turned our stomachs for over a year now, she links the movement to history and finds at its root a deep anger - at being ignored, oppressed, held down, and disbelieved for far too long. i think this a super worthwhile read, and on tuesday i hope that the anger at the core of the book helps bring us across a very blue finish line. #vote #bookstagram #bookstagrammer #bookshelf #book #books #igbook #bookish #bookaddict #vote #election2018 #womensmarch #womenvote #voting #midterms #thelastweekend #gotv #igbooks #igreads #instabooks #instabook

text:
i have spent over 10,000.00 in therapy in the past ten years to heal from rape. ten thousand dollars, folks. and tbh i've needed every goddamn session.
*
*
*
*
it was money that was saved for the purpose of funding my education by my very not-rich family and my very not-rich self. this money,  instead, was spent on keeping me alive after men worked their power issues out on my body instead of in a therapy office. *
*
*
so men, next time you dodge therapy because you're scared, or because the consequences of your problems aren't debhilitating enough to see the need for support -despite your partner probs  pleading that you see a therapist; a ubiquitous phenomena in cis-hetero relationships - shut the fuck up and book a therapy appointment and do your work. *
*
*
*
 women are sick of spending their time and money dealing with what patriarchy did to you, and in turn us; be it lowkey ignorance about your inner world or high levels of violence - it's all patriarchy . if you don't work on your shit, you are leaving whatever bullshit you bring into this world to women to cope with. *
*
*
lead by example and start putting the onus back on men to be accountable for their problems. ignoring them makes the load heavier for women, even if you think its benign - it is not benign. but you know what is? therapy.

text:
and when you have nothing else and it's just you and your practice and you're exhausted, you're drained and you're emotionally mentally and physically spent find yourself a piece of music that speaks to your soul... and let it move you. 
look beyond the pain... look beyond your shaking arms and dig deep into the place where your last reserves of strength reside and set them free... i know that these videos don't look like much and there are certainly far greater yogi's out there with far more experience, more strength, more flexibility, more openness... but my time on the mat is the closest i ever get to my truest self and i am grateful for every single moment i am able to experience that.

i feel beautiful and strong and powerful and capable and nothing can take that from me.

text:
luk røven, morten fucking pape…
i januar besluttede jeg sammen med danmarksindsamlingen at sætte et navn i mine 6. roman til salg til højestbydende til fordel for hjemløse børn. hurtigt steg buddene og det kulminerede med 10.500 kroner. en dag fik jeg denne mail: 
kære jesper
i dag kom postbuddet endelig forbi i med et brev, jeg længe har glædet mig til at få. her fremgår det, at jeg skal kontakte dig og fortælle, at det er mig, der skal optræde ved navns nævnelse i din næste bog.
det gør jeg hermed. 
det var nervepirrende til det sidste at følge auktionen forrige weekend på min lauritz-app, mens jeg sad iklædt kradsende, færøsk sweater, tynde briller på næsetippen og en smilende silkeabe på skulderen, udklædt som dyrehandler clausen fra huset på christianshavn til en fastelavnsfest i min kammerats kollektiv på østerbro. 
det holdt hårdt og vi måtte ud i flere ekstra, stædige budrunder, men i sidste ende måtte min navnløse rival i cyperspace opgive ævred og kapitulere. jublen var stor i kollektivet, både blandt de andre, men i særdeleshed hos jeg, da det blev offentliggjort at jeg havde vundet auktionen. 
jeg vil gerne takke dig for din villighed til ofre dig i kunsten for de hjemløse børn, som jeg glædeligt nu donerer 10.500 kroner til.
jeg glæder mig umådelig meget til at læse den næste omgang løjer med axel steen og den karakter, som nu skal navngives efter mig. håber ikke det bliver en alt for perfid og usympatisk karakter, det blir spændende. 
rigtig mange gode weekendhilsner,
morten 
kære morten
du er den cooleste kat, der har sat sine ben på amager. fuck, hvor er det her optur. jeg glæder mig vildt til at finde en karakter til dig, har flere muligheder, hvad er værst? strømer eller forbryder?
kh 
hej jesper, 
jeg skal helst ikke være panser, det’ sikkert. det er ikke så coolkat at være det, der hvor jeg kommer fra. 
alt derudover er godt. måske førsteelskeren. den kriminelle mastermind. ham med den største gun. eller den med den opklarende åbenbaring. måske ham der bliver kronvidnet. eller den som dækker over det endelige spor. det kunne også være en rigtig lortet #metoo-type. 
kh morten :-) #axelsteen6 @politikensforlag @mortenpape

wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
out of all my tattoos, this one is the most special one to me. anyone who knows the #semicolonproject knows it has to do with mental illness, particularly suicide. i loved that it meant my story was not over and that i could find the strengthen to carry on. ➖

what i didn't expect though, was to be asked questions about it. tattoos can have such a deep meaning most times and i felt that if anyone knew what it meant, they would spot it and simply carry on with their lives. as a lecturer right now, that isn't the case. "chef awande, i saw your tattoo. do you also have mental health issues?"
i first hesitate to respond, but having told myself to me honest, i say "yes" and smile.
"me too," they will say and then proceed to let me know how less alone they feel knowing that i can publicly walk around with my tattoo. ➖

as honest as i am, i still have moments of discomfort thinking about how i come across to other people with my history of mental illness, in patient treatment and suicidal thoughts. i have relapsed and i have had to climb out of it. but then i realise that maybe, just maybe i've made some kind of difference with just a small permanent drawing on my body. someone feels they can talk to me and i can be a support. and even though the creator behind it couldn't fight her own demons, that her will to try at some point, did help others. 
#mentalillness #mentalhealth #anxiety #depression #semicolontattoo #semicolon #ptsd #relapse #tattoo #support #bekindtoyourself #selflove #life #powerfulmind #alone #notalone #metoo #mind #keepgoing #tough

text_retweet:
de her to ❤️❤️ #repost @jesper_stein
・・・
luk røven, morten fucking pape…
i januar besluttede jeg sammen med danmarksindsamlingen at sætte et navn i mine 6. roman til salg til højestbydende til fordel for hjemløse børn. hurtigt steg buddene og det kulminerede med 10.500 kroner. en dag fik jeg denne mail: 
kære jesper
i dag kom postbuddet endelig forbi i med et brev, jeg længe har glædet mig til at få. her fremgår det, at jeg skal kontakte dig og fortælle, at det er mig, der skal optræde ved navns nævnelse i din næste bog.
det gør jeg hermed. 
det var nervepirrende til det sidste at følge auktionen forrige weekend på min lauritz-app, mens jeg sad iklædt kradsende, færøsk sweater, tynde briller på næsetippen og en smilende silkeabe på skulderen, udklædt som dyrehandler clausen fra huset på christianshavn til en fastelavnsfest i min kammerats kollektiv på østerbro. 
det holdt hårdt og vi måtte ud i flere ekstra, stædige budrunder, men i sidste ende måtte min navnløse rival i cyperspace opgive ævred og kapitulere. jublen var stor i kollektivet, både blandt de andre, men i særdeleshed hos jeg, da det blev offentliggjort at jeg havde vundet auktionen. 
jeg vil gerne takke dig for din villighed til ofre dig i kunsten for de hjemløse børn, som jeg glædeligt nu donerer 10.500 kroner til.
jeg glæder mig umådelig meget til at læse den næste omgang løjer med axel steen og den karakter, som nu skal navngives efter mig. håber ikke det bliver en alt for perfid og usympatisk karakter, det blir spændende. 
rigtig mange gode weekendhilsner,
morten 
kære morten
du er den cooleste kat, der har sat sine ben på amager. fuck, hvor er det her optur. jeg glæder mig vildt til at finde en karakter til dig, har flere muligheder, hvad er værst? strømer eller forbryder?
kh 
hej jesper, 
jeg skal helst ikke være panser, det’ sikkert. det er ikke så coolkat at være det, der hvor jeg kommer fra. 
alt derudover er godt. måske førsteelskeren. den kriminelle mastermind. ham med den største gun. eller den med den opklarende åbenbaring. måske ham der bliver kronvidnet. eller den som dækker over det endelige spor. det kunne også være en rigtig lortet #metoo-type. 
kh morten :-) #axelsteen6 @politikens

text:
we all have been through stuff and made mistakes along the way. i’m here to say, its okay! 💯🙌 .
sometimes you can feel guilt and shame over things of the past. today is a new day. let it go and let’s begin!
.
don’t take it with you. no you can’t change it, but your story and your truth (even if it’s not so good) might just be what someone else needs to hear to learn from you.
.
let’s help lead this next generation to success in business, in relationships, in life! let’s help teach them from what we’ve already been through and to stand up for our beliefs.

text:
#metoo movement in china: powerful yet fragile
the movement is growing in china despite obstructions by a sensitive state, indifferent public and misogynist elites.

since last january, china has been experiencing a firestorm against sexual predation that reached universities, media outlets, sports teams, ngos and even religious temples. more than 20 liberal intellectuals, media personalities and activists have now been accused of sexual misconduct, and several publicly shamed university professors have been dismissed. china's ministry of education has pledged to implement institutional mechanisms to prevent sexual harassment at universities and the country's top legislative is considering adding protections against sexual harassment into the civil code.

read the full story by al jazeera at https://bit.ly/2sbgzob ⚠️⛑️if you or someone you know in china needs help, please call 119 for emergency assistance (120 for an ambulance) or call the china women's federation activist public service hotline at 12338

text_retweet:
tw: rape and abuse. this speech is the most moving thing i have seen in my life. when i watched it for the first time i cried. and i cried many times after that. her story is so incredibly emotional and the scary part is, every woman i know has a story like hers. hell, there are parts that i relate to and i am only a teenager. because some things are is extreme as what she has gone through, and some are as little as being catcalled on the street. both of these things though, are so damaging to a woman’s mental and physical health and so violating. i am also a gymnast so the story about the gymnasts and the medical resident rlly hit close to home cause i’ve experienced something similar. just creepy people showing up to watch girls in tight leotards. it makes me sick. and the fucking president doing nothing about it. no statement. nothing. i think people everywhere need to see this speech and understand what women go through. halsey is so strong and courageous. thank you @iamhalsey for sharing your story with us. i hope people take something away from this speech. i hope women feel empowered to speak their truths and they know they r not alone. if u read to here u r the real mvp. if u repost plz credit cause cutting these took forever

text: triggers are real, and in many cases misunderstood. when a survivor experiences a trigger/episode, they loose track of their surrounding, and “relive” a particular traumatic event they. in this case, the survivor continuously lives with fear, and would rather die, cause self harm, use drugs to escape their pain, rather than continue to relive the pain triggers, and their past abuse causes over and over again. learning about triggers, and their effects will help you better support your child, or loved one who is a survivor. #buddyspeaks #metoo #endchildhoodsexualabuse #trauma #emotionaltrauma #boys #girls #survivors #pain #knife #mentalhealth #life #survivor #endthestigma #ptsd #depression #abuse #selfharm #suicidal #therapy #recovery #csaqt #stopabuse #children
